{"build_type":"library","description":"Run a host command and capture everything it writes to stdout and stderr. Creates a pipe, forks, in the child redirects fd 1 and fd 2 onto the pipe write end and execve-s argv[0] with the given argv and envp (exit_group 1 if execve fails), and in the parent closes the write end, drains the read end into the caller buffer until end of stream, reaps the child via wait4, stores the child exit code in g_host_command_exit_status, null-terminates the buffer, and returns the captured byte count. Pipe descriptors and the exit code are read as single bytes (scale-4 reads are unreliable): the descriptors at offsets 0 and 4, the exit code at wait-status byte 1 (a clean exit leaves the code in the second byte). The sole sanctioned exec point for the stock systemd CLIs in the systemd compatibility layer.","module_name":"execute-host-command-capturing-standard-output","package_name":"execute-host-command-capturing-standard-output","function_definitions":{"execute-host-command-capturing-standard-output":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"argv","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"envp","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"out_buf","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"out_cap","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","s